node.text: We closed on our new house today! 🎉I can’t believe it! What a whirlwind the last two months have been! I wanted to give you a full home tour of the empty house before we move in this weekend Stay tuned until the very end...that’s when I share the big project we have planned for the house and one of the main reasons why we decided to move! We can’t wait to move in, get settled, and begin sharing this new adventure with all of you! ❤️🏡

node.text:
Today I’m sharing a walk through of my entire house (every single room!), which I’ve actually never done before on my page! I’m sharing rooms I’ve never shown before including my laundry room and mud room! 

If you missed it, we are selling our house! Get all the info on our move on my website, Mytexashouse.com. All sources are linked on the LIKEtoKNOW.it app or by clicking the link in my IG bio!

*update: House sold. We moved! 

#hometour #realestate #houseforsale #mytexashouse #texashomes #texasrealestate #falldecor #homedecor

node.title: We’re Selling Our House!: A Complete Home Tour of “Mytexashouse”!

node.text: Here’s my super easy way to put on a duvet cover! No more actually climbing inside of the duvet to install it! 🙈😂 The first step, which isn’t shown, is to turn the duvet cover INSIDE OUT! Then lay the duvet insert over the cover and tie all four sides of the duvet to the insert! Roll them like a burrito. Turn back out the ends like a sandwich baggie, and then voila!✨...the duvet cover is perfectly placed on the duvet in under 2 minutes!🙌🏻 And you can do this technique on your bed instead of the floor if you want. 😉 Link to products/outfit: http://liketk.it/2LMSl

node.title: How to put on a duvet cover in under 2 minutes!

node.text: This is a beautiful home we toured today by Darling Homes in the Montgomery Farms neighborhood in Allen, TX. This is a 4 bedroom home (option for 5th bedroom) with about 5,000 square feet of living space. My favorite part of the home was the large open living room and kitchen space with all the floor to ceiling windows overlooking the patio! I also LOVE that there was a huge pantry and even a prep kitchen! Check out the IGTV video for the full tour of this beautiful home! What is your favorite part of this home?!!

node.title: Model Home Tour: Darling Homes, Allen, TX (priced from: $900K+)

node.text:
This model home is in Arlington, Texas (right near Dallas. TX). This is a Toll Brothers Home in the Viridian master planned community. The model is called the “Valen”. It has 5 bedrooms, and around 4000+ sq feet. The starting price of this home is around $615K, but upgraded as shown in this model would be between $800K to $900K. Website: https://www.tollbrothers.com/luxury-homes-for-sale/Texas/Viridian?amp=true
**I’m not a realtor, just show these model tours for fun!

Head here to shop >>> https://mytexashouse.com/mytexashouse-by-orian-rug-collection/

I recently toured this beautiful modern farmhouse style home in Parker, Texas in the Whitestone Estates neighborhood. It is a one story home, on a one acre lot and has a 3 car garage, 4 bedrooms and is approx 4500 square feet. A spec home in this neighborhood, similar to the model, is selling for $823K.
Mytexashouse.com

node.title: Model Home Tour: Parker, TX (Shaddock Homes, $800k+, 4500 sq ft)

node.text:
This model home is by Huntington Homes and located in Prosper, TX in the Windsong Ranch neighborhood. Due to time limitations I couldn’t include the upstairs area which had a game room, wet bar, and full bed and bathroom. Check out Huntington’s website for floor plan, pictures of the upstairs and more info. 
https://www.huntingtonhomestx.com/dfw/prosper/windsong-ranch/410-032

node.text: We toured the Vanguard Mediterranean model by Toll Brothers in the beautiful master planned community of Travisso in Leander, TX (outside of Austin, TX). This model starts at $615K, but many options can be added such as a stand-alone casita. As shown, this home would be at least $820K.

node.text: We recently toured this beautiful model home in Frisco, TX by Shaddock Homes. It is located in the Villages of Stonelake Estates and has a starting price of $622K for the 4 bedroom version. This model has 5 bedrooms and approximately 4,000 square feet. *I am not a realtor or associated with this home builder at all. Just like to tour homes for interior design ideas! www.Mytexashouse.com

node.title: Model Home Tour: Frisco, TX (Shaddock Homes, price: from $622K+)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by My Texas House | Erin on August 01, 2021. May be an image of living room.

node.text:
Sale Alert!! 🚨 I just saw that the Jessie rug from my collection is on big sale at Walmart right now! The 9x13 is an amazing price at only $265!! One thing though….the listing for the Jessie rug on walmart.com is a little off! It is listed as the “My Texas House Striped rug” instead of Jessie for some reason. And also a sweet follower informed me that the listing is showing 4 color options, when there’s only actually two colors (natural and natural/gray!)….but it’s just that there’s 2 natural and 2 gray options. I know, super confusing! 😆🤷‍♀️ All the rugs are in stock though!!! Let me know if you have any trouble when you’re trying to order! I’m sure we will get it fixed, but in the meantime I didn’t want you to miss out on an amazing sale!!🤗

We leave for Maui tomorrow morning! Eeeeek! I’ll be sure post lots of pics from our trip in my stories! 🏝😎 And all my sources are linked on the LTK app!! http://liketk.it/3l0jP

I finally started packing for our trip to Hawaii! I think I may have to double check my suitcase for a stowaway though! 😆 Jessie was none too pleased when she saw the suitcases out again! 🥺 I think I got most of what I need packed….aside from my toiletries and some casual outfits (and Jessie 😉). 

Sharing some of my favorite must-haves for my trip in my stories today! Can’t wait to get my feet in that sand! It’s been 20 years since I’ve been to Hawaii!! Eeeeek! Come on Monday!🤗✈️🏝😎

Shop my bedroom decor and Hawaii outfits on the LTK app! http://liketk.it/3kWAT

#travel #packing #vacation #hawaii #anniversarytrip #maui #swimsuits #onepieceswimsuit #sandals #beachwear #bedroom

node.text:
I need your opinions! In my stories today I shared how I’m stumped about what to do with Kayla’s room and the weird curved wall (you can kind of see it off to the right in this pic). It’s curved because the other side is our curved staircase, but it creates a little design dilemma for me! I wanted to do board and batten in here or possibly a pretty wallpaper (I included a pic of Kayla’s old room to show the beautiful wallpaper mural she used to have!!) 

But the curved wall makes it look a little off centered in the room and I’m wondering if I just go ahead with my plans for the back feature wall ignoring the curved part…or do I create some sort of feature on the curved wall to make it stand out? In my stories, the issue is more evident so it will make more sense. 

Anyone have curved walls in their homes? Any ideas of how to handle them?? 

I’ve linked all bedroom sources, including the gorgeous blue and white striped Avery comforter set from my Walmart collection (and it’s BACK IN STOCK IN KING SIZE!) on the LTK app!! http://liketk.it/3kPdp

We’ve been spending all our time in here lately watching the Olympics! Have you been watching? This is the first year all 3 of my kids are mesmerized by it all! I think seeing kids their own age competing…especially in the skateboarding competitions has really made a big impact on them! They are all planning what event they are going to go for!☺️ Jason - taekwondo, Ashley - fencing, archery or wrestling, Kayla - skateboarding or gymnastics, Dusty - soccer or golf, Me - Trampoline (if my bladder could hold out)🤸😂 or maybe equestrian 🐎! 

What event would you do if you could be in the Olympics?!

I’m sharing my media room sources on the LTK app and in my stories today! http://liketk.it/3kwwq
